Key Match Events: Denmark and Serbia played out a goalless draw.
Jonas Wind's goal for Denmark was disallowed by VAR.
Joachim Andersen's own goal for Serbia was disallowed.
Jannik Vestergaard's powerful header was saved by the Serbian goalkeeper.
Aleksandar Mitrovic missed a crucial chance to score for Serbia in the 81st minute.
Predrag Rajkovic made three crucial saves for Serbia.
Post-Match Reflections: Denmark progresses to the knockout round of Euro 2024.
Serbia is eliminated from the tournament with two points from three matches.
Denmark will face Germany in the next round.
